The paper deals with the concept of entropy and its computational variants in the context of information leakage and chain rules. This makes it relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including cryptography (cs.CR), information theory (cs.IT), computational complexity (cs.CC), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and machine learning (cs.LG). However, since the paper focuses on the security implications of entropy and leakage, cs.CR is the most likely sub-category.
